# Home Lab

A personal cybersecurity lab built for hands-on practice with real attack and defense techniques.

---

## Setup

| Component | Details |
|---|---|
| Host Machine | Dell Optiplex 7060 (repurposed) — Intel i7-8700, 16GB RAM, 1TB SSD |
| Hypervisor | Proxmox VE (enterprise-grade bare-metal hypervisor) |
| Attacker VM | Kali Linux |
| Target VMs | Metasploitable 2, DVWA on Debian (Damn Vulnerable Web Application) |
| Network | Isolated virtual network (no internet exposure) |

---

## Completed Exercises

### Apache Continuum — Remote Code Execution → Root
**Target:** Metasploitable 2 (port 8080)  
**Tool:** Metasploit / Meterpreter  
**Result:** Gained root shell on target machine

**Summary:**
- Scanned Metasploitable with Nmap, identified Apache Continuum running on port 8080
- Searched Metasploit for a matching module and configured the exploit
- Launched exploit, received a Meterpreter shell, confirmed root privileges with `getuid` and `sysinfo`

